  "prompt": "Do PS3 Move controllers work on PS4 VR?",
  "response": "Yes, PlayStation Move controllers are compatible with the PlayStation VR (PS4 VR) system. The PS Move controllers were originally designed for the PlayStation 3 but were adapted for use with the PS4 and its VR capabilities. They are often used as motion controllers for certain PS VR games, offering a more immersive experience by allowing players to interact with the virtual environment using hand gestures and movements.\n\nHowever, not all PS VR games support the Move controllers\u2014it depends on the game. Some games use the standard DualShock 4 controller, while others may require or support the Move controllers for enhanced gameplay. Additionally, some games may work with both options. Be sure to check the specific game's requirements or recommendations for controller compatibility.",
